defaultI have interviewed families who have lost a loved one to 
defaultv
defaultCJD
default who had also been a blood donor, they were warned by the CJD unit and Department of Health officials ‘don’t tell anyone your child gave blood especially the press or your neighbours.’ These family members were terrified by the very officials who were supposed to offer help and support. This is a common theme in my personal and professional dealings with families who have been affected by 
defaultv
defaultCJD
default. They have been kept isolated by government officials, many bullied this is totally unacceptable. 
